{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Criminals exploit these characteristics in various ways.",
    "Mixing services, or tumblers, are used to mix transactions from multiple users, obscuring the original source of funds (Chohan, 2017; Shojaeenasab, Motamed and Bahrak, 2020).",
    "Privacy coins, like Monero, Dash, and Zcash, offer enhanced privacy and anonymity, making it nearly impossible to trace the flow of funds (Stojan, 2023).",
    "Layering is another technique, involving moving funds through multiple transactions and accounts to obscure the original source (Mooij, 2023).",
    "Criminals may also use multiple wallets and exchanges to transfer funds, making it challenging for authorities to track the flow of money (Nowroozi et al., 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
